main event: A round object, 2 feet in diameter, was observed in Rochester, New York on November 7, 1957.
interesting points: The object was bright white and had jet exhaust., The object circled about to the northwest., The observation lasted for 5 minutes., Local observatory directors were called to observe but did not see anything unusual., The sighting remains unexplained.
sighted object: a round bright white object with jet exhaust
witness description: no witnesses reported seeing the object
